    <sec>
      <title>Bicluster Detection</title>
      <p>Given a normalized gene expression matrix, <italic>V</italic> = (<italic>X, Y</italic>), with a set of rows <italic>X</italic> = {<italic>x</italic><sub>1</sub>, ‚Ä¶, <italic>x</italic><sub><italic>N</italic></sub>}, a set of columns <italic>Y</italic> = {<italic>y</italic><sub>1</sub>, ‚Ä¶<italic>y</italic><sub><italic>M</italic></sub>}, and the element <italic>v</italic><sub><italic>ij</italic></sub> ‚àà <italic>V</italic> represents the expression value of gene <italic>i</italic> in sample <italic>j</italic>. A bicluster <italic>B</italic> = (<italic>I, J</italic>) is a <italic>n</italic> √ó <italic>m</italic> submatrix of <italic>V</italic>, where <italic>I</italic> = (<italic>i</italic><sub>1</sub>, ‚Ä¶<italic>i</italic><sub><italic>n</italic></sub>) ‚äÇ <italic>X</italic> is a subset of genes and <italic>J</italic> = (<italic>j</italic><sub>1</sub>, ‚Ä¶<italic>j</italic><sub><italic>m</italic></sub>)‚äÇ<italic>Y</italic> is a subset of samples. The biclustering aims to identify a set of biclusters <italic>B</italic> = {<italic>B</italic><sub>1</sub>, ‚Ä¶<italic>B</italic><sub><italic>s</italic></sub>} such that each bicluster <italic>B</italic><sub><italic>k</italic></sub> = (<italic>I</italic><sub><italic>k</italic></sub>, <italic>J</italic><sub><italic>k</italic></sub>) satisfies specific homogeneity criteria. The RFN model is a single or stacked factor analysis model as in Equation (1), which extracts the covariance structure of the data.</p>
      <disp-formula id="E1">
        <label>(1)</label>
        <mml:math id="M1">
          <mml:mtable class="eqnarray" columnalign="left">
            <mml:mtr>
              <mml:mtd>
                <mml:mi>V</mml:mi>
                <mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
                <mml:mi>W</mml:mi>
                <mml:mi>h</mml:mi>
                <mml:mo>+</mml:mo>
                <mml:mi>Œµ</mml:mi>
              </mml:mtd>
            </mml:mtr>
          </mml:mtable>
        </mml:math>
      </disp-formula>
      <p>where <italic>V</italic> = {<italic>V</italic><sub>1</sub>, ‚Ä¶<italic>V</italic><sub><italic>N</italic></sub>) is the input data (visible units), <italic>h</italic> ~ <italic>N</italic>(0, <italic>I</italic>) is the hidden unit (where <italic>N</italic> is a normal distribution), <italic>W</italic> is the weight matrix, Œµ ~ ‚Ñï(0, Œ•) is the noise error vector, and Œ• is the noise covariance matrix. The parameters of the model are <italic>W</italic> and Œ•. If <italic>h</italic> is given, then only the noise Œµ is a random variable and we have <italic>V</italic>|<italic>h</italic> ~ <italic>N</italic>(<italic>Wh</italic>, Œ•).</p>
      <p>Let <italic>E</italic> denote the expectation of the data including the prior distribution of the factors and the noise distribution. We can get <italic>E</italic>(<italic>VV</italic><sup><italic>T</italic></sup>) = <italic>WW</italic><sup><italic>T</italic></sup> + Œ•. The marginal distribution for <italic>V</italic> is <italic>V</italic> ~ <italic>N</italic>(0, <italic>WW</italic><sup><italic>T</italic></sup> + Œ•). The log-likelihood of the input data is given in Equation (2).</p>
      <disp-formula id="E2">
        <label>(2)</label>
        <mml:math id="M2">
          <mml:mtable class="eqnarray" columnalign="left">
            <mml:mtr>
              <mml:mtd>
                <mml:mi>log</mml:mi>
                <mml:mstyle displaystyle="true">
                  <mml:msubsup>
                    <mml:mo>‚àè</mml:mo>
                    <mml:mrow>
                      <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                      <mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
                      <mml:mn>1</mml:mn>
                    </mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mi>n</mml:mi>
                  </mml:msubsup>
                  <mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mi>p</mml:mi>
                    <mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo>
                    <mml:msub>
                      <mml:mi>V</mml:mi>
                      <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                    </mml:msub>
                    <mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo>
                  </mml:mrow>
                </mml:mstyle>
                <mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
                <mml:mo>‚àí</mml:mo>
                <mml:mfrac>
                  <mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mi>n</mml:mi>
                    <mml:mi>m</mml:mi>
                  </mml:mrow>
                  <mml:mn>2</mml:mn>
                </mml:mfrac>
                <mml:mi>log</mml:mi>
                <mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo>
                <mml:mn>2</mml:mn>
                <mml:mi>œÄ</mml:mi>
                <mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo>
                <mml:mo>‚àí</mml:mo>
                <mml:mfrac>
                  <mml:mi>n</mml:mi>
                  <mml:mn>2</mml:mn>
                </mml:mfrac>
                <mml:mi>log</mml:mi>
                <mml:mo>|</mml:mo>
                <mml:mi>W</mml:mi>
                <mml:msup>
                  <mml:mi>W</mml:mi>
                  <mml:mi>T</mml:mi>
                </mml:msup>
                <mml:mo>+</mml:mo>
                <mml:mo>Œ•</mml:mo>
                <mml:mo>|</mml:mo>
              </mml:mtd>
            </mml:mtr>
            <mml:mtr>
              <mml:mtd>
                <mml:mtext>¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†</mml:mtext>
                <mml:mo>‚àí</mml:mo>
                <mml:mfrac>
                  <mml:mn>1</mml:mn>
                  <mml:mn>2</mml:mn>
                </mml:mfrac>
                <mml:mstyle displaystyle="true">
                  <mml:msubsup>
                    <mml:mo>‚àë</mml:mo>
                    <mml:mrow>
                      <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                      <mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
                      <mml:mn>1</mml:mn>
                    </mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mi>n</mml:mi>
                  </mml:msubsup>
                  <mml:mrow>
                    <mml:msubsup>
                      <mml:mi>V</mml:mi>
                      <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                      <mml:mi>T</mml:mi>
                    </mml:msubsup>
                  </mml:mrow>
                </mml:mstyle>
                <mml:msup>
                  <mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mo>(</mml:mo>
                    <mml:mrow>
                      <mml:mi>W</mml:mi>
                      <mml:msup>
                        <mml:mi>W</mml:mi>
                        <mml:mi>T</mml:mi>
                      </mml:msup>
                      <mml:mo>+</mml:mo>
                      <mml:mo>Œ•</mml:mo>
                    </mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mo>)</mml:mo>
                  </mml:mrow>
                  <mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mo>‚àí</mml:mo>
                    <mml:mn>1</mml:mn>
                  </mml:mrow>
                </mml:msup>
                <mml:msub>
                  <mml:mi>V</mml:mi>
                  <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                </mml:msub>
              </mml:mtd>
            </mml:mtr>
          </mml:mtable>
        </mml:math>
      </disp-formula>
      <p>For the mean-centered input vector <italic>V</italic>, the posterior <italic>p</italic>(<italic>h</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub>|<italic>V</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub>) is Gaussian with the mean vector (<sub><italic>u</italic><sub><italic>p</italic></sub>)<italic>i</italic></sub> and covariance matrix <italic>K</italic><sub><italic>pp</italic></sub> as in Equation (3):</p>
      <disp-formula id="E3">
        <label>(3)</label>
        <mml:math id="M3">
          <mml:mtable class="eqnarray" columnalign="left">
            <mml:mtr>
              <mml:mtd>
                <mml:msub>
                  <mml:mrow>
                    <mml:mrow>
                      <mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo>
                      <mml:mrow>
                        <mml:msub>
